.TH SWAY-SIMPLE-OVERLAY 1 "2026-03-26" "sway-simple-overlay" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
sway-simple-overlay \- lightweight on-screen overlay for Sway and wlroots Wayland compositors
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B sway-simple-overlay
[\fB\-\-config\fR \fIPATH\fR]
[\fB\-\-css\fR \fIPATH\fR]
[\fB\-\-no\-reload\fR]
[\fB\-\-debug\fR]
[\fB\-\-quiet\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B sway-simple-overlay
is a multi-monitor, live-updating overlay for Sway and wlroots-based Wayland
compositors, built with Python and GTK3.
It renders an always-on-top overlay panel on one or more monitors displaying
the current time, date, or the standard output of arbitrary shell commands.
The overlay is fully configurable via a YAML file and styleable via GTK CSS,
and supports live reloading of both files without restarting.
.PP
The overlay is implemented using the
.B gtk-layer-shell
protocol and requires no XWayland.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-\-config " " \fIPATH\fR
Path to the configuration file (YAML).
Overrides the default search order.
.TP
.BR \-\-css " " \fIPATH\fR
Path to the stylesheet (CSS).
Overrides the default search order and the \fIcss_path\fR value in the
configuration file.
.TP
.B \-\-no\-reload
Disable live reload.
By default, changes to
.I config.yaml
or
.I style.css
are applied automatically.
This flag disables that behaviour regardless of the \fIlive_reload\fR setting
in the configuration file.
.TP
.B \-\-debug
Enable verbose debug logging to standard error.
.TP
.B \-\-quiet
Suppress all log output except errors.
.SH CONFIGURATION
.SS File lookup order
The configuration file
.RI ( config.yaml )
is searched in the following locations, in order:
.IP 1. 4
The directory containing the
.B sway-simple-overlay
script/executable.
.IP 2. 4
.IR $XDG_CONFIG_HOME /sway-simple-overlay/config.yaml
(defaults to
.IR ~/.config/sway-simple-overlay/config.yaml ).
.PP
The stylesheet
.RI ( style.css )
is searched in the same locations unless overridden by \fIcss_path\fR in the
configuration file or by the \fB\-\-css\fR command-line option.
.SS Top-level keys
.TP
.B monitors
List of per-monitor configuration objects.
See the
.B MONITOR CONFIGURATION
section below.
.TP
.B css_path
Optional path to the CSS stylesheet.
If unset, the default search order described above is used.
.TP
.B live_reload
Boolean (\fItrue\fR / \fIfalse\fR).
When \fItrue\fR (the default), the overlay watches
.I config.yaml
and the CSS file for changes and reloads them automatically.
.SS Monitor configuration
Each entry in the \fImonitors\fR list accepts the following keys:
.TP
.B name
Sway output name (e.g.\ \fIDP\-1\fR, \fIeDP\-1\fR) or the special value
\fIdefault\fR, which acts as a fallback for any monitor that does not match a
named entry.
.TP
.B anchor
List of screen edges to anchor the overlay to.
Accepted values: \fItop\fR, \fIbottom\fR, \fIleft\fR, \fIright\fR.
.TP
.B margin
Two-element list \fI[vertical, horizontal]\fR specifying the margin from the
anchored edges in pixels.
.TP
.B scale
Floating-point font scaling factor applied to this monitor.
.TP
.B refresh_interval
Seconds between content updates.
Fractional values (e.g.\ \fI0.5\fR) are accepted.
.TP
.B parts
List of content items to display.
See the
.B PARTS
section below.
.SS Parts
Each item in the \fIparts\fR list creates one label in the overlay.
.TP
.B name
Identifier for the part; also used as the CSS class applied to the label
widget (e.g.\ \fItime\fR, \fIdate\fR, \fIcpu\fR).
.TP
.B format
.BR strftime (3)
format string.
Used when the part represents a time or date value.
.TP
.B command
Shell command whose standard output becomes the label text.
The command is executed via \fI/bin/sh \-c\fR.
Avoid slow commands as they block the overlay UI refresh.
.SH STYLING
The overlay uses standard GTK3 CSS.
Each part corresponds to a CSS class with the same name as the part.
The wrapping box widget has the CSS id \fB#clock\-box\fR.
.PP
Example:
.PP
.RS 4
.nf
#clock-box {
    background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.35);
    padding: 10px;
    border-radius: 10px;
}

\&.time {
    color: #00ffcc;
    font-size: 28px;
    font-weight: bold;
}

\&.date {
    color: #888888;
    font-size: 16px;
}

\&.cpu {
    color: #ffcc00;
    font-size: 18px;
}
.fi
.RE
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/sway-simple-overlay/config.yaml
Default user configuration file.
.TP
.I ~/.config/sway-simple-overlay/style.css
Default user stylesheet.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B XDG_CONFIG_HOME
Base directory for user configuration files.
Defaults to
.I ~/.config
when unset.
.SH EXAMPLES
Start the overlay with default configuration:
.PP
.RS 4
.B sway-simple-overlay
.RE
.PP
Use a custom configuration file:
.PP
.RS 4
.B sway-simple-overlay \-\-config /path/to/my-config.yaml
.RE
.PP
Use a custom stylesheet and disable live reload:
.PP
.RS 4
.B sway-simple-overlay \-\-css /path/to/my-style.css \-\-no\-reload
.RE
.PP
Start with debug output:
.PP
.RS 4
.B sway-simple-overlay \-\-debug
.RE
.PP
Example
.I config.yaml
showing two monitors:
.PP
.RS 4
.nf
monitors:
  - name: "DP-1"
    anchor: ["top", "right"]
    margin: [20, 20]
    scale: 1.2
    refresh_interval: 1.0
    parts:
      - name: "time"
        format: "%H:%M:%S"
      - name: "date"
        format: "%Y-%m-%d"
      - name: "cpu"
        command: "grep 'cpu ' /proc/stat | awk '{usage=($2+$4)*100/($2+$4+$5)} END {print int(usage) \"%\"}'"
  - name: "default"
    anchor: ["top", "left"]
    margin: [10, 10]
    scale: 1.0
    refresh_interval: 5.0
    parts:
      - name: "time"
        format: "%H:%M"

css_path: "style.css"
live_reload: true
.fi
.RE
.SH NOTES
.IP \(bu 2
The overlay is always rendered on top of all windows.
Click-through (pointer event passthrough) is not implemented.
.IP \(bu 2
Slow shell commands (high latency) will block the overlay UI refresh cycle.
Keep
.B command
values fast.
.IP \(bu 2
.B sway-simple-overlay
is designed primarily for Sway.
It may partially work on other wlroots-based compositors that implement the
layer-shell protocol, but is not officially supported on them.
.SH DEPENDENCIES
.TP
.B Python 3.8+
Runtime interpreter.
.TP
.B GTK 3
Graphical toolkit (\fIpython3-gi\fR, \fIgir1.2-gtk-3.0\fR).
.TP
.B gtk-layer-shell
Wayland layer-shell protocol bindings (\fIgir1.2-gtk-layer-shell-0.1\fR).
.TP
.B PyYAML
YAML configuration parser.
.TP
.B swaymsg
Used at runtime to query connected outputs from the Sway IPC socket.
